Use `@ExtendWith(SpringExtension.class)` with `@Import(MessagingConfig.class)` and `@TestPropertySource` to provide the required property values:
```java
// @ExtendWith(SpringExtension.class)
// @Import(MessagingConfig.class)
// @TestPropertySource(properties = "kafka.bootstrap-servers=localhost:9092")
// class MessagingConfigTest {
//     @Autowired KafkaTemplate<String, OrderEvent> kafkaTemplate;
//
//     @Test void templateIsCreated() { assertThat(kafkaTemplate).isNotNull(); }
// }
```
This loads only `MessagingConfig` and its declared dependencies — no full app context, no web server. Startup takes milliseconds. For pure unit testing without Spring at all, call the `@Bean` methods directly as regular Java methods: `var factory = new MessagingConfig().producerFactory("localhost:9092")`.

